ORDER OF IMPLEMENTATION
master > tabs > editor > picker > menu > sidebar > status > notifications > projects  > zettelkasten
- there needs to be an interface for clients("cli") and another for master to be inside of clients ("parent") .

MASTER
- add-clients methods processes a string containing names and specifications for opening clients ...
  - it's once at the start, with the starting arguments ...  
  - example of argument: "editor:a.log/14.10.2026 picker:b.rec d.fami/everything-and-all" ...
  - "today" and "tomorrow" shall open "a.log/(data de hoje)" in a new editor tab ...
- listens for the filesystem's module loading channel . and sends the page pointer to a receiver function inside a client that matches the specification(method getSpec() in cli interface) with the path ...
- listens for the routine's module resizing channel . and processes it to update all clients (updating bounds) ...
  - resizing uses a struct called Boundaries, that contains the fullsize, available size and starting pos, that can be used to set actualpos and actualsize in each client ...
- listens for the routine's module inputting channel . and processes it to update all clients (input) ...
- filesystem can be called from anywhere within the master ...
- utilities can be used anywhere within the master to generate partial frames and queues ...
- the drawing method is used to compose the final queue (uses utilities) ...
- at last, and the engine module's asynchronous pipeline is called from within the drawing method ...
- drawing needs to run whenever a state is updated ...
- drawing depends on mode being "monocle"(the middle area is dedicated to the single focused client) or "fibonacci"(the screen is divided for more than one client to fit at the same time, following a fibonacci based positions and sizes distribution) ...

TABS
- can be on or off ...
- can be "monocle"(only one tabs bar at the top) or "fibonacci"(a bar at the top of each client (will need getClients() from parent interface)) ...
- in monocle mode: the first line at the top contains a list of information about every single one of the not-fixed open clients . 
- in fibonacci mode: on the top of each client, a line is reserved for showing information about that client ... 
- pressing "tab" toggles the "switching mode" ...
- in the switching mode, you can:
  - move focus with left and right arrows in the keyboard ... 
  - and move the currently focus with ctrl+left and ctrl+right arrows in the keyboard ...
  - and quick switch(change focus to and quit switching) by pressing "asdfghjklqwertyuiopzxcvbnm" characters, where each one is assigned to a tab based in the order ...
- monocle mode's information when not in switching mode: - a symbol for the type of client, and the name of the client (picker, zettelkasten...) . and specially for editor: just the symbol and the path ...
  * for paths in tabs, if they are too long, make them shorter by doing like: "d.fami/.../nice-good" or "d.fami/...is-really-good..."
- monocle mode's information with switching mode on: the symbol is replaced by a quick switching letter, and the information shown is the name (picker, zettelkasten...) and ":spec", like: "a picker:a.log  s editor:a.log/14.06.2026"
  - the tabs shall smoothly alternate between background color ... 
- fibonacci mode's information with switching mode off: the same as for monocle, but with the title centered in each adn every bar ...
- when in monocle, let a second line show with a line which tab is selected ...

EDITOR
- occupies all the available space ... 
- zenmode makes the content of  the editor occupy only 65% of the screen and be centralized . and makes there be no numbers ...
- line wrapping is always on .
- numbers at the left of each line can be or not .
- not current lines show syntax highlighting, and hide highlighting characters ...
- current line also shows syntax highglighting, but keeps the highlighting characters ...
- about the syntax highlighting ...
  - toggle bold(*), italic(%), underline(_), almost($), all(&), uppercase(^) ...
  - metadata keys (before ":" in a line: "time: 25.10.2002") are bold ...
  - #tags e #projects are bold ...
  - timestamps are bold ...
  - within blocks of text that start with > or ` or = or ~ ...
    - all lines have a different background color ...
    - the header line (first) has is bold ...
  - within isolated lines that start with -- or ~~ ...
    - what comes before the "|", is bold . if there is no "|", nothing is bold ...
- as the actual first line, before the first line of content, there needs to be the relative path of the opened page and a symbol containing its "stage"(will talk about stages when i get to picker) ...
  - if you edit this line, you can change the path (when saved with ctrl+s with cursor right above it (will talk about this in ctrl+s)) - if deep with children, takes them all with it to the new path ...
- a viewport needs to be applied that cuts the lines in a way that makes the height of the selected line correpond to how far within the total page content lines we are (the shall be a margin for the start and end of the content not to be cut right at the starting or ending lines) ...
- about inputting ! ...
  - characters and space add characters to cursor position like in normal editors ... also moves cursor .
  - backspace erases a character to the left and moves the cursor, and moves cursor to previous line if cursor is at the start . but if the line is empty, and the cursor is at the start, backspace shall not move to previous line ...
  - ctrl+backspace erases into the the closest previous space character, or at the start of the line if space is not found . also moves cursor .
  - enter, if at the very end of a line, creates a next one below . and if at the middle of a line, also creates a next line below, and carries with it, all the text to the right of the cursor ... also moves cursor .
  - ctrl+enter, always creates a new line below ... also moves cursor .
  - delete erases a character to the right and does not move cursor ...
  - ctrl+delete erases until the next space to the right or until end of line, and does not move cursor .
  - arrows up and down: move cursory up and down ...
  - ctrl+arrows up and down: move the current line up and down ...
  - arrows left and right: move cursorx one to the left or one to  the right . when it gets to the start and end of the line, jumps to next or previous line ...
  - ctrl+arrows left and right: move to the previous and next space accurence, or end or start if not found, of a line ...
  - ctrl+z and ctrl+y: undo and redo ...
  - ctrl+x: cuts a line (can be pasted later) ...
  - ctrl+c and ctrl+v: copies and pastes lines that where saved ... - copying and pasting shall work across different editors that are opened ...
  - ctrl+d: duplicated a line right below ...
  - * ctrl+s updates the stage of the opened page by editing its content and path . and also does some special things ...
    - if ctrl+s is pressed when the cursor is within the first line (containing the path of the page of the editor), there shall be an attempt to rename or repath the page (right after editing its content as it is now in the rest of the opened editor lines) . if the attemp of renaming or repathing goes wrong, the name shall update back to how it was before the edit attempt ...
    - if ctrl+s is anywhere else, it just applied the content from the editor to the page, as a "stage" of "edited" ...
    - if ctrl+s is pressed within a block that starts with > or ~ or = or ` ...
      - make sure / generate a second line to the block like "id: abcdef123456", that is, a line staring with "id:" and containing a 12 digit id (may need to generate) ...
    - for all blocks (4 cases): if the block has a header starting with one of the symbols i told you, after the symbol there is some text, and after the text, there is a #something or a @something, and a valid id line, and at least one more line of text (3 or more total), we go to the next step ...
      - the next step is creating a draft at the right place (in filesystem's cache) ...
        - for ` , it's "c.rand/`a-name-for-it#idea-one" - that is within c.rand ...
        - for ~ or = or > , it's "b.rec/>a-name-for-it@project-one" - that is within b.rec ...
      - when a block is valid as itself, it needs to be checked for if there is already a page for it (with the same id as metadata) ...
        - if there is none, "a new page shall be staged" in cache, "as draft", and containing all information demonstrated by this template:

        * titulo: symbol + name + @ or # + owner . example: >the-name@project-1
        id: {id(second line)}
        name: {name(header in the middle, with dashes)}
        kind: {kind(does not appear in "`" block) - can be: plan(>), session(=) or task(~)}
        time: {time(last time context within the a.log that was saved)}
        owner: {owner(first #something text at "`" block, or @something in any other)}
        tags: {tags(list of #tags like: tag1, tag2, tag3) - or empty}
        projects: {projects(list of @projects like: proj1, proj2, proj3)}
        measurement: {measurement()}
        hidden: {hidden(if there is a "!" between the first symbol of the block header and the name text, show "yes", if not, show "no")}
        modified: no(default) - can be manually set to yes or no ...
        ---
        {content} - it's only synced from right after id lines (upon saving within it in a.log), of the block in a.log, if "hidden is set to no by the exclamation mark", and, modified is also no ...
    - if you change any information within the a.log and save from within the block, the block pages are updated . but "the title and metadata editing depend on the hidden and modified logic" (as i said above) .
    - if ctrl+s os pressed within an isolated line that starts with "--" or "~~" ...
      - "-- free text blah blah" shall become "-- abcd1234 | free text blah blah" . where abcd1234 is an id of 8 digits ...
      - and this message needs to be synced (stage edit) to a page . for -- , "c.rand/.reminders", and for ~~, "b.rec/.reminders" ...
        - always keep the first line empty and check if a message with same id is already there . if not, you can add it at the top like this:
        
        -- message blah blah blah sdofijhposfdijg  poisjdpo  ifjgpoisdfjg poisf ...
        #acd1234
        * empty line

    * all block and special-line automation and styling and shall onlt be recognized and done in a.log pages ...

    - continuing ...
    - ctrl+s with no new changes, does not just update the content and stage to edited ... it syncs the page (then, there is a notification with a 5 seconds countdown that the user can cancel with ctrl+z (for later)) ... 
    - ctrl+enter on an id of block opens the block in a new editor tab .
    - ctrl+enter on the id of a special line, opens the corresponding .reminders ...
    * reminders entries can be edited manually, and as long as they have the original id, they shall not be overwritten (if manually changed) ...
    - ctrl+enter in @projects opens the project in editor (if does not exist, do nothing) ...
    - ctrl+enter in #tag opens a zettelkasten with spec of tag ...
    - ctrl+enter in a timestamp opens a.log/dd.mm.yyyy even if it does not exist yes (draft...) ...

PICKER
- components:
- prompt on bottom left where you can write whatever you want ...
- an inverted list (bottom to top) panel on the left of "items" ...
- a preview panel at the right side ...
- stores a searching mode: current context or recusively within ...
- stores a searching-score method: fuzzy, literal ...
- stores a sorting mode(for when there is no prompt): basic(deep first or alphabetic), time(title or metadata containing time/timestamp) , priority(metadata of int) ...
- the default starting context (set as spec when using "master's add-clients"), contains the surface of prsnl.spc ...
  - a.log, b.rec, c.rand, d.fami, e.proj, .resources ... (and whatever more in the future) ...
  - this context needs to always start sorted as basic .
  - a.log start sorted with decreasing time (stamp found in title)
  - b.rec and c.rand also, but the time is found in metadata ...
  - d.fami is basic all over it, no matter how deep the context ...
  - e.proj is based on decreasing priority (metadata of type int) ...
    - within each project, it's basic again ...   
- within each level, except the surface of prsnl.spc, there needs to be a first item called "...", that responds to enter by navigating one level up ...
- inputs:
  - enter navigates ...
  - ctrl+enter shows a menu with options (try to implement a general menu with this specific one) ...
- the options are:
  - * doom, doom branch, undoom, sync, sync branch, apisync, apisync branch, open in editor, read and read fresh .
* branched options only appear to deep items that have children ...
* undoom shall be the first option of a doom item, and only show for it ...
- the stages of pages are ...
  - ghost, local, api, edit, draft, doom, conflict .
- how the menu appears for each stage (order):
  - ghost: read fresh, read fresh branch(if deep and has children) .
  - local: open in editor, apisync, apisync branch(if deep and has children), doom, doom branch (if deep and has children) .
  - api: open in editor, synclocal, synclocal branch(or not), doom, doom branch (if deep and has children) .
  - edit: open in editor, synclocal, synclocal branch(or not), doom, doom branch (if deep and has children) .
  - draft: open in editor, synclocal, synclocal branch(or not), doom, doom branch(or not) .
  - doom: undoom, synclocal, synclocal branch(or not) .
  - conflict: open in editor, synclocal, synclocal branch(or not), syncapi, syncapi branch(or not) .
* reading, sync local and api sync resolve all stages:
  - reading makes ghosts become sync (local or api) , and brings more pages ...
  - sync deletes doomed ...
  - sync make edit and draft synced (local or api) .
  - * api sync make conflicts may be generated (contain information to edit manually) ...
  *** syncing shall not happen instantaneously . it acts and sends a notification on  top right and waits 5 seconds. if the user presses ctrl+z, it undoes the operation and the cache is restored to how it was before ...
  *** reading updates ghosts, apis and locals, only . and adds unknown items if there are ... - it works the same way as sycing (can be undo within 5 seconds and notifation...) ...
- each stage has a symbol for it ...
- sem prompt, a lista de itens deve mostrar doom, conflict, draft e edit antes, nessa ordem
- with no prompt, the list of items shall show conflicted, doomed, edited and draft items, before, in this order ...
- each page item in list has a stage symbol on the right ...
- and an identity symbol on the left (uppercase greek letters for deep ones and lowercase greek letters for shallow) ...
* the preview window needs to show every information that has changed from Og of the same page . and the content (or diff if the content has been modified drom Og) ...
- editing path, name and content is done in editor! creating and changing type is done in picker ...
  - add a last item to the menu of items called "toggle type", that changes the type of the page item from shallow to deep or deep to shallow ...
  - pressing the "..." item with ctrl+enter opens a menu for draft creation . you type a name in the menu's prompt and it is created and opened in editor (new tab) .
* "..." only appears with no prompt ...
* the modes stored as states (sorting, context and scoring-method) in picker can be seen in the status bar at the bottom (implement later...) ...
* in picker, in the surface of d.fami and e.proj there shall also be an option, besides creating a shallow draft, for creating a new project and creating a new family, "when pressing ctrl+enter in ..." !!
* each item needs to have a score from -1.00 to +1.00 visible when prompted ...
* filtering is like a sorting, it does not exclude any option, just makes it far away and closer to -1.00 ...

