PROJECTS
- contains a prompt at the bottom left, a list of items and a shared area ...
- the first look is an empty prompt and a list containing one item for each of the projects from e.proj ...
- this first surface is sorted by the metadata priority, decreasingly ...
- enter navigates and ctrl+enter opens actions menu - just like in picker ...
- when you enter a project, you see 3 options in this order ...
  - .last-plan: it's the page for the last plan of the this project. a preview of it is shown on the right side panel (shared area) ...
  - .templates: you can enter to find a list of whatever is inside of this project's actual folder (templates) . they are also shown on the right side when selected . they are sorted basic ...
  - .events: a vision of all the "b.rec" pages that are owned by the current project we are in . you can see them in the shared panel when selected. and they are sorted by decresing time metadata ...
- within the surface, there shall be a "new project" item as the first one ... - creates a basic structure for a project and its first plan, and opens in editor ...
- within the templates surface, there shall be a "new template" item ... - opens in editor new tab, a new draft with the surface of the project ...
*** now i need the funcionality in projects ...
- enter navigates and ctrl+enter does actions ...
- in the projects surface, ctrl+enter opens it in editor in another tab .
- "+ new project" responds to ctrl+enter by creating a project and a first plan for it ...
